MeshCore
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Project:    MeshCore — open-source LoRa mesh firmware/protocol
Source:     https://github.com/meshcore-dev/MeshCore
Copyright:  Copyright (c) 2025 Scott Powell / rippleradios.com
License:    MIT License (see below)

`protocol/` is a byte-exact Rust port of the MeshCore v1.15.0 wire protocol
(packet framing, header/route/payload-type fields, path-hash encoding, the
Ed25519/X25519/AES-128-ECB/HMAC-SHA256 crypto and identity primitives, the
DM/ACK codec, and symmetric channel encryption) — see `protocol/src/lib.rs`
for the module map and interop rationale. MeshCadet exists to be a fully
compliant MeshCore citizen on the air; this interop is a hard project
requirement (see `docs/adr/0001-charter.md`).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
RadioLib
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Project:    RadioLib — universal wireless communication library for Arduino/PlatformIO
Source:     https://github.com/jgromes/RadioLib
Copyright:  Copyright (c) 2018 Jan Gromeš
License:    MIT License (see below)

`firmware/src/radio.rs` bring-up sequencing for the SX1262 radio (TCXO
voltage/delay, regulator mode, PA clamping fix-up, calibration image bytes,
sync-word register values) mirrors RadioLib's `SX126x`/`SX1262` C++ driver
behavior, specifically `src/helpers/SX126XLT.cpp` (referenced at commit
`dee3e26a` of the MeshCore tree that vendors it), so that MeshCadet's radio
bring-up matches what deployed stock MeshCore nodes (which build against
RadioLib) do on the air. See `firmware/src/radio.rs`'s module doc for the
full source-reference list.

