Third-party Rust crate dependencies
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
MeshCadet's Cargo dependency graph (protocol/host/xtask/ui_sim/ui_perf at
the workspace root, and the detached firmware/ workspace) pulls in several
hundred third-party crates, each under its own license (overwhelmingly
MIT/Apache-2.0/BSD/Zlib-family permissive terms). None of them require
reproducing their license text in this NOTICE file (none impose a
NOTICE-file obligation the way Apache-2.0's own recommended practice
does for its dependents, and no crate in the graph carries an Apache-2.0
NOTICE file of its own to propagate). The full audit — every crate, its
resolved version, and its SPDX license expression, plus the GPLv3
compatibility reasoning — is recorded in `docs/licensing/DEPENDENCY-AUDIT.md`
and `docs/licensing/THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md`.

